FBIS4-68191 "jptot021__l94057" JPRS-TOT-94-021-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 15 May 1994 WEST EUROPE TURKEY Interior Minister Gives PKK Surrender Numbers Interior Minister Gives PKK Surrender Numbers TA1505153494 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 GMT 15 May 94 TA1505153494 Ankara TRT Television Network Turkish BFN [Announcer-read report] [Excerpts] Interior Minister Nahit Mentese has said that the fight against the separatist terrorist organization PKK [Workers Party of Kurdistan] is continuing successfully and added that there is a 300 percent increase in the number terrorists who surrendered in the first four months of 1994 in comparison to the same period last year. [passage omitted] Mentese stated that 500 terrorists -- 186 terrorists killed, four wounded -- were captured in operations conducted against the dissipating terrorist organization during 1-15 May. Mentese added that 197 long-barreled rifles, 37 revolvers, 386 bombs, and large quantities of ammunition were seized during these operations. Explaining that collective surrenders, including members in high- level positions, were taking place for the first time, Mentese stressed that during this period 48 terrorists -- 22 in Sirnak and 7 in Agri and Van [as heard] -- surrendered to the security forces, handing in their weapons. Mentese said that collective surrenders from the terrorist organization's militant cadres in the mountainous region are expected to increase. [passage omitted]
